x_1
x_2
p\left(x_1,x_2\right)=p\left(x_1\right)\cdot p\left(x_2\right)
p\left(x_1,\left.x_2\right|\theta \right)=p\left(\left.x_1\right|\theta \right)\cdot p\left(\left.x_2\right|\theta \right)
p\left(x_1,x_2\right)=p\left(x_1\right)\cdot p\left(x_2\right)
 \int p\left(x_1,\left.x_2\right|\theta \right)p(\theta )d\theta =\int p\left(\left.x_1\right|\theta \right)p(\theta )d\theta \cdot \int p\left(\left.x_2\right|\theta \right)p(\theta )d\theta
p\left(x_1,\left.x_2\right|\theta \right)=p\left(\left.x_1\right|\theta \right)p\left(\left.x_2\right|\theta \right)
\therefore \int p\left(\left.x_1\right|\theta \right)p\left(\left.x_2\right|\theta \right)p(\theta )d\theta =\int p\left(\left.x_1\right|\theta \right)p(\theta )d\theta \cdot \int p\left(\left.x_2\right|\theta \right)p(\theta )d\theta
